  "text": "KM is implemented as a runtime including a set of KM daemons (Fig.13) . Each local site has one KM daemon that is responsible for processing both local and remote requests. One site of the system is chosen as a host to store the meta-knowledge repository. An example of searching/retrieving is shown in Fig.13 . The search operation is composed of four steps: (1) a request is sent to the Host to look for the meta-knowledge needed. Then, this will be retrieved (2) and sent back to the source site (3), and it extracts the results as meta-knowledge objects [CITATION_1] . The retrieving operation is also composed of four steps: (1) requests are sent to the appropriate sites; (2) retrieve the knowledge found at each site; (3) send back to the source site via KM Daemon; (4) extracts results as knowledge objects.",
